Let the exp grind begin!

Welcome to the era of Kunark! We had some success getting people Seb keyed as a raid last night. With many different EXP groups going on at once make sure to stay vocal in guild chat and get your spot! Lots of us have boxes in groups that we would gladly kick to welcome a guildmate. I personally plan on spending every moment of non-raid time I can exp grinding.

Regarding Epics:

Don't forget to update your epic progress on the guild tracker! Lemaitre has been so kind as to create an excel spreadsheet for us to track. This is not only important so that guildies can see who will need help, but also because raid dropped epic items will use your completion % as a component for determining who wins the bid.

We Killed Vox!

Cold As Ice
Things We Did Well
  • Killed her on attempt #2!
  • Pulled a bunch of bears right through Lady Vox' chamber (kind of succesfully even!)
  • Adjusted buffs, focused, and improved our DPS greatly on the second attempt.
  • Tank heals were excellent!
Areas of Improvement
  • Bind outside of the AOC. If you don't bind you need to start porting/running back IMMEDIATELY.
    I know sometimes people forget and that is fine, but don't just sit and wait on a drag/rez.

    If the reason you aren't binding is because it's inconvenient, please consider that 40+ people are waiting on you.

  • Maybe don't troll Vack when he's had 2 hours of sleep (oops)
Buffs & Mana Management

I wanted to make a separate section for this topic. It is often a problem with certain classes that they will be low on mana from buffing the raid There are a few things everyone can do to help mitigate these issues.

  • Proper targets: While it's nice to have everyone buffed to the gills, it isn't always viable.
    An important thing to know is which classes NEED which buffs.
    For example, Symbol / AC are probably only needed on tanks & charm pets. The priority should probably be Warriors > Hybrids = Charm Pet Owners.
  • Proper timing: The next thing we can do to save mana is properly timing our buffs. If you know we're going to be sitting for 20 minutes on a corpse recovery you should prioritize gaining mana, and avoid casting buffs until closer to pull time. This applies DOUBLY SO for short term buffs such as haste.
  • SITTING DOWN: This is absolutely the most important thing. I cant count the number of times I've seen someone say they are OOM while standing up. It may seem like a minor thing but it is in fact HUGE. I rarely run out of mana on buffing classes compared to my counterparts and I attribute this to the fact that if it is an option, I am ALWAYS sitting down.
